On Escalation Ticket # 00424321 the new comment has been added: Csaba-Janos Polyanki:

@WaitingOnEngineer

Hi! This is the same issue that was found in https://dev.azure.com/NetwrixCorporation/CoSoSys-EPP/_workitems/edit/342009. @Mara Dobse  fixed it and it applies here too. 
Custom build can be found here: \192.168.14.5Publicgroups_daily_buildsCoSoSys2024-builds2024_11_08EPPClient_v6.2.4.0026
The problem is that Outlook uses the same helper process "msedgewebview2_exe" when sending a mail as Teams does. The workoround is to identify the destination and if we detect "Outlook", simply change the process name. 

@Cristian-Alexandru Halmajan  @Krzysztof Staszalek  please help us with a download link. Thanks!

Hi! This is the same issue that was found in https://dev.azure.com/NetwrixCorporation/CoSoSys-EPP/_workitems/edit/342009. @Mara Dobse  fixed it and it applies here too. 
Custom build can be found here: \192.168.14.5Publicgroups_daily_buildsCoSoSys2024-builds2024_11_08EPPClient_v6.2.4.0026
The problem is that Outlook uses the same helper process "msedgewebview2_exe" when sending a mail as Teams does. The workoround is to identify the destination and if we detect "Outlook", simply change the process name. 

@Cristian-Alexandru Halmajan  @Krzysztof Staszalek  please help us with a download link. Thanks!

On Escalation Ticket # 00424321 the new comment has been added: Cristian-Alexandru Halmajan:

Hi @WaitingOnEngineer,

Please use the following link to download the test build:
https://download.endpointprotector.com/custom_agent/Epp08112024/EPPClient_v6.2.4.0026.zip

Please be aware that this should be treated as a test build and only installed on a couple of machines, for testing purposes.

Regards,
Cristi
